---
import { homeClasses, homeDerivedClasses } from "../../lib/homeClasses";

const { container, h2, lead, bulletItem, dotAmber } = homeClasses;
const { cardP6 } = homeDerivedClasses;
---

<section class="py-12" id="getting-started" aria-label="Getting started">
  <div class={container}>
    <h2 class={h2}>Getting started</h2>
    <p class={lead}>
      If you’re a collector sending valuable cards, the main question is “what happens before I ship
      anything?” This is the flow from first message to cards back in hand.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-8 grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-3">
      <div class={cardP6}>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-amber-950">1) Email photos first</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-amber-900/80">
          Send a few clear photos and a short description of the damage and your goal (display,
          collection, or grading). We’ll reply with next steps and whether restoration looks realistic.
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-amber-900/80">
          <li class={bulletItem}>
            <span class={dotAmber}></span>
            <span>Front + back, straight-on</span>
          </li>
          <li class={bulletItem}>
            <span class={dotAmber}></span>
            <span>Close-ups of bends/creases/edge issues</span>
          </li>
          <li class={bulletItem}>
            <span class={dotAmber}></span>
            <span>Any prior damage notes (water, smoke, adhesive, etc.)</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class={cardP6}>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-amber-950">2) We send shipping instructions</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-amber-900/80">
          After we review your photos, we’ll confirm if we can take the job and share the exact
          shipping address and packing checklist. This prevents surprise shipments and reduces risk
          in transit.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-amber-900/70">
          We strongly recommend tracked shipping. For higher-value cards, consider insurance and
          signature on delivery.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class={cardP6}>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-amber-950">3) Inspection → plan → approval</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-amber-900/80">
          Once your cards arrive, we do a close inspection and send a restoration plan with risks and
          recommendations. <strong class="font-semibold text-amber-950">No work starts until you approve</strong>.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-amber-900/70">
          If you decide not to proceed, we can return your cards. Details are shared with your plan so
          you can make a clear call.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class={`mt-6 ${cardP6}`}>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-amber-950">Typical response time</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-amber-900/80">
        We reply to new requests within <strong class="font-semibold text-amber-950">1–2 business days</strong>.
        If you have a deadline (event, gift, show), mention it in your email and we’ll tell you what’s
        realistic.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

